20personal%20data%20from%20the%20EU%20to%20China.%3Cp%3EJens%20B%C3%BCttner%2Fpicture%20alliance%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EEU%20regulators%20hit%20TikTok%20with%20a%20%24600%20million%20fine%20for%20unlawful%20data%20transfers%20to%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey%20said%20TikTok%20failed%20to%20ensure%20EU-level%20data%20protection%20under%20Chinese%20law.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20social%20media%20giant%20said%20on%20Friday%20that%20it%20disagreed%20with%20the%20fine%20and%20planned%20to%20appeal.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EEuropean%20regulators%20have%20fined%20TikTok%20%24600%20million%20after%20concluding%20that%20the%20social%20media%20giant%20unlawfully%20transferred%20users'%20personal%20data%20from%20the%20EU%20to%20China%20and%20failed%20to%20meet%20key%20transparency%20obligations%20under%20European%20data%20privacy%20laws.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIreland's%20Data%20Protection%20Commission%2C%20which%20acts%20as%20the%20lead%20EU%20watchdog%20for%20many%20global%20tech%20firms%20headquartered%20in%20Dublin%2C%20led%20the%20investigation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20said%20TikTok%20failed%20to%20ensure%20that%20data%20accessed%20by%20employees%20in%20China%20was%20protected%20at%20a%20level%20%26quot%3Bessentially%20equivalent%26quot%3B%20to%20EU%20standards%2C%20as%20required%20under%20the%20General%20Data%20Protection%20Regulation%20(GDPR).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERegulators%20also%20said%20the%20company%20misled%20users%20by%20failing%20to%20name%20China%20as%20a%20data%20destination%20and%20not%20disclosing%20the%20extent%20of%20remote%20access%20from%20countries%20like%20China%2C%20breaching%20GDPR's%20transparency%20rules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%20of%20TikTok's%20failure%20to%20undertake%20the%20necessary%20assessments%2C%20TikTok%20did%20not%20address%20potential%20access%20by%20Chinese%20authorities%20to%20EEA%20personal%20data%20under%20Chinese%20anti-terrorism%2C%20counter-espionage%2C%20and%20other%20laws%20identified%20by%20TikTok%20as%20materially%20diverging%20from%20EU%20standards%2C%26quot%3B%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20Graham%20Doyle%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%24600%20million%20penalty%20includes%20about%20%24550%20million%20for%20unlawful%20data%20transfers%20and%20about%20%2450%20million%20for%20transparency%20violations.%20The%20penalty%20is%20the%20third-largest%20ever%20under%20the%20GDPR%20and%20part%20of%20a%20growing%20European%20scrutiny%20targeting%20Big%20Tech's%20data%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETikTok%20may%20face%20a%20suspension%20of%20data%20transfers%20to%20China%20if%20it%20doesn't%20comply%20within%20six%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20month%2C%20TikTok%20acknowledged%20that%20limited%20European%20user%20data%20had%20been%20stored%20on%20servers%20in%20China%2C%20contrary%20to%20previous%20claims%2C%20and%20that%20it%20has%20since%20been%20deleted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20a%20statement%20on%20Friday%2C%20the%20social%20media%20giant%20said%20it%20disagreed%20with%20the%20decision%20and%20plans%20to%20appeal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristine%20Grahn%2C%20TikTok's%20head%20of%20public%20policy%20and%20government%20relations%2C%20said%20the%20ruling%20overlooks%20significant%20reforms%20introduced%20under%20its%20%26quot%3BProject%20Clover%26quot%3B%20data%20security%20initiative.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20TikTok%20has%20never%20received%20or%20complied%20with%20a%20request%20for%20European%20user%20data%20from%20Chinese%20authorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20TikTok's%20first%20major%20penalty.%20In%202023%2C%20Ireland's%20Data%20Protection%20Commission%20fined%20it%C2%A0%24368%20million%C2%A0for%20failing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiktok-fined-368m-in-europe-for-failing-to-protect-childrens-privacy-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotect%20children's%20data%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20year%2C%20Meta%20was%20fined%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3